The mystery Ivanivka: There are *so many* Ivanivkas. Today
column4: there were reports that Russia shelled an Ivanivka and that Ukraine repelled an attack that came from the direction of an Ivanivka. I assumed it was the southern Ivanivka on this map (3).

name: later in the day
description: I got confirmation from a Russian source that the more northern Ivanivka (blue arrow) was heavily shelled by Ukrainian forces (which would make sense if Russia was attacking from there).

WKT: Note that this northern Ivanivka has the "fortified town" marker. This is a built up base the Russians have been using for a while now. Also note that there are Ukrainian forces just west (Mospanove and Yavirske) that appear to have been static for weeks now. They aren't static.
If I piece together the information from Russian sources and Ukrainian sources
name: it makes me wonder if Ukraine is getting close to attacking this northern Ivanivka? As opposed to the more southern one? Or perhaps both?! Why are there so many Ivanivkas?!

description: I saw no comments on the Russian offensive actions out of Mazanivka and towards Krasnopillya or Bohorodychne today
column4: but I assume they proceeded as per usual: lots of casualties and no success.
